form_title.ms_form_title_llm_v1: Quality Assurance Checklist, Task B - CONTINUED CASES CHECKLIST

full_text: Screened by NARA, 5/5/2023 A 41 623 672 Quality Assurance Checklist Office Code LOS Task B - CONTINUED CASES CHECK LIST Yes No N/A Comments 1. Was the N-400 Processing Worksheet completed to show whether applicant appeared for interview? 2. Is reason for continuation clearly indicated on the N-400 Processing Worksheet? 3. If reexamination for Sec 312 eligibility, does the N-400 Processing Worksheet indicate that the case has been rescheduled within 90 days after initial interview? 4. If claiming a disability exception, and the N-648 submitted was not acceptable, does N-400 Processing Worksheet indicate that a supplemental disability determination was requested? 5. Was application signed by applicant at time of interview? INTERVIEW was Not completed. 6. Was application signed by officer at time of interview? 7. Were the N-400 questions which were asked by DAO and answered during the interview checked off or circled in red ink? 8a. Were all annotations/changes made by DAO noted on the N-400 attestation in red ink, 8b. and numbered in red ink? 9. Are all signatures correct? 10. Has any necessary additional documentation been requested on an N-14? 11. If so, does the N-14 give the applicant a due date to submit the additional documentation? 12. Did the N-400 Processing Worksheet contain the results of WAIVEd, the FBI fingerprint check prior to the time of interview? Rev.5/23/97 Attachment 13 J Reviewer's Signature Welong 10-01-98 (Date) USE SEPARATE SHEET FOR ADDITIONAL COMMENTS (Include on separate sheet: Task B (con't), A#, Reviewer's signature, and date)
